entry.title: Cycloneminx
entry.content:
No.025: Cycloneminx

Price: US$ 750

Mechanism: Deep cut face turning deltoidal hexecontahedron

Axis of Rotation: 60 axes

Diameter (inner): 130 mm

Material: PETG (FDM)

First Completion Date: 2024-08-26

Cycloneminx is the most crazy puzzle I’ve ever made, the size comes to 130mm face-to-face, and it has 16 kinds of parts,842 parts in total, 852 pices of stickers. Although it has so many parts, it turns very smoothly and satisfyingly. As it’s a jumbling only puzzle, it might be a little difficult to scrmble it.

Here’s the turning demo: https://youtu.be/biGn_DFSoWg?si=nCLDp32RzGljqMHh

Pictures

Note

The price is for the puzzle along with one set of stickers. I will assemble and break in the puzzle for you, and you’ll need to sticker it yourself. Contact me via Instagram or email with any needs or questions.

entry.title: Collider Dodecahedron
entry.content:
No.S01: Collider Dodecahedron

Price: US$ 240

Mechanism: Face turning pentakis dodecahedron

Axis of Rotation: 60 axes

Diameter (inner): 90 mm

Material: PETG (FDM)

First Completion Date: 2024-06-07

Collider Dodecahedron was originally designed by David Pitcher, but due to the difficulty of assembling his version, he did not sell it. Now I’ve designed my version and have Dave’s permission to sell this puzzle, thanks to Dave’s generosity!

Here’s the turning demo: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fBj6di1cQVI
